LET THE HIGH PRAISES OF GOD BE IN YOUR MOUTH
#
The God of New beginnings will start something new in your life in Jesus Name.
#
TEXT: Psl. 22:3; Gen. 46:26-29; 38:12-30; Psl. 149:6

And though Judah was the strongest of his brothers and a ruler came from him, the rights of the firstborn belonged to Joseph (1 Chron. 5:2)
The God of New beginnings will start something new in your life in Jesus Name.
Beloved, let us not start this year with unnecessary anxiety. Dont get caught up by fear, that possibly what you have been trusting God will not be done.
If anything that is supposed to have happened has not happened, do not worry yourself for nothing; because there is a God that is in charge. However, this God dwells in the midst of the praises of His people. (Psl. 22:3)
There is something about giving God high praises. Whenever you want a radical change; and judgment upon your enemies, what you need is high praises.
After Joseph had gone ahead to Egypt, followed by the drama of how he and his wicked brothers met again; he finally ordered that his father, and all his household should relocate to Egypt. Now, as Jacob and the over seventy members of his household left Canaan land, and came to Egypt, Jacob sent Judah to go before him. (Gen. 46:26  29)
Why Judah? Because Judah carries praise. And the man that carries praise, carries God! In this month, you will praise God non  stop, then hitherto impossible situations will shift. I heard of a woman who praised God for 7 hours daily, for 21 days. Her 18 years of barrenness gave way to fruitfulness. She became pregnant! 
Do you know that even when Judah messed up, in respect of committing incest with his daughter-in-law, God did not cast him away? (Gen. 38:12-30) That we see David messing up with women is an inherited gene from Judah! But, notwithstanding this genetic weakness, because of being a high-praiser of God, Judah still produced the Messiah! 

